theorem Topology.closure_inter_dense_open_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A U : Set X}
    (hA : Dense (A : Set X)) (hU : IsOpen U) :
    closure (A ∩ U : Set X) = closure U := by
  classical
  -- First inclusion: monotonicity of `closure`.
  have h₁ : closure (A ∩ U : Set X) ⊆ closure U :=
    closure_mono (by
      intro x hx
      exact hx.2)
  -- Second inclusion: use density of `A`.
  have h₂ : closure U ⊆ closure (A ∩ U : Set X) := by
    intro x hxU
    -- Show `x ∈ closure (A ∩ U)`.
    have : (x : X) ∈ closure (A ∩ U : Set X) := by
      refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
      intro V hV hxV
      -- Because `x ∈ closure U`, `V` meets `U`.
      have hVU : ((V ∩ U) : Set X).Nonempty := by
        have := (mem_closure_iff).1 hxU V hV hxV
        simpa [Set.inter_comm, Set.inter_left_comm, Set.inter_assoc] using this
      -- `V ∩ U` is open and non-empty.
      have hVU_open : IsOpen (V ∩ U) := IsOpen.inter hV hU
      -- Density of `A` gives a point in `A ∩ V ∩ U`.
      have h_nonempty : ((V ∩ U) ∩ A : Set X).Nonempty :=
        hA.inter_open_nonempty hVU_open hVU
      -- Rearrange intersections to the required form.
      simpa [Set.inter_comm, Set.inter_left_comm, Set.inter_assoc] using h_nonempty
    exact this
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.nonempty_inter_of_dense_and_open
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A U : Set X}
    (hA : Dense (A : Set X)) (hU_open : IsOpen U) (hU_nonempty : (U : Set X).Nonempty) :
    (A ∩ U).Nonempty := by
  -- `Dense.inter_open_nonempty` immediately gives the desired result.
  exact hA.inter_open_nonempty hU_open hU_nonempty

theorem Topology.closureInterior_interior_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (interior A)) = closure (interior A) := by
  simpa [interior_interior]
